stories.text: It seems like the industry is ripe for consolidation and Apple obviously needs to increase its library while at the same time it seems like Netflix is going to be struggling against emerging competitors like Disney, Paramount, etc. for at least a few years. Plus Apple has a ton of cash on hand that they don't seem to be leveraging so 'buying the dip' right now might be a worthwhile strategy.
